The paper deals with the problem of learning from compressed observations, which involves encoding the Y-part of the sample at a finite bit rate. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with statistical learning, which is a core topic in Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses nonparametric regression, which is a common topic in Data Structures (cs.DS). The paper's focus on achieving optimal performance suggests that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper's use of Gaussian noise suggests that it may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
